r />&gt; disconnected dentries on the list.  Only dentries obtained with<br />&gt; d_obtain_root() are now stored on this list.  There are many fewer of<br />&gt; these (only NFS and NILFS2 use the call, and only during filesystem<br />&gt; mount) so contention on the bit-lock will not be a problem.<br /><br />Thanks, Neil. This is much nicer than the magical special case patch<br />for s_anon bitlock.<br /><br />Al, I'm going to assume I'll get this through your vfs tree (with<br />whatever edits from the comments people made).<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
